    %h2 Product Design
    %p
      By combining empathy, creativity and rationality, I aim to understand and
      solve problems in a human centered way, such that the resulting solutions
      are always useful, usable and desirable. Below is an overview and some
      examples of how I apply design thinking to building software.

    %h3 Design Thinking
    %p
      At the highest level, a design driven processes can be broken into three
      broad phases: developing an understanding of the problem, exploring
      solution concepts and identifying which solutions address the problem
      best.

    %h3 Understanding
    %p
      The better we understand the problem, the people with the problem and the
      situation in which they experience the problem, the more capable we are of
      building powerful solutions.
    %p
      A product design process that internalizes the power of understanding is
      not only a core driver of innovation but also a defensible business
      strategy. Aesthetics and functionalities can always be copied but the
      insights and perspectives that lead to great products are nearly
      impossible to replicate.

    %h3 Exploration
    %p
      Sometimes your first idea might be the best solution, but isn’t never the
      only possible one. With creative exercises teams can leverage their
      insights and understandings to generate many solution concepts and uncover
      opportunities that may have otherwise never been discovered.
    %p
      If we don’t go beyond what we already know, into the unknown, we limit our
      ability to discover radically new opportunities.

    %h3 Determining Fitness
    %p
      Through qualitative and quantitative testing we can determine which ideas
      work best and confidently focus on refining and implementing the most
      appropriate solutions.
    %p
      Every design challenge is unique and as a result a strong design processes
      needs to be able to adapt as things change. Being able to identifying when
      a tactic or strategy isn’t working and then taking a different approach,
      is central to facilitating this adaptability.

